Coxal gills (Fig. 1) present on P3-P5, rounded to ovoid. Oostegites (Figs 1, 3
B'
) on P3-P4, short, subrectangular and shorter than corresponding coxal gill, each with one long slender seta.

Pereiopods 5-7 (Fig. 3
C-E
) progressively longer towards posterior; basis of P5-P6 broad, that of P7 slender. P7 with one of distal armature elements on distolateral angle of carpus modified into a crooked comb-like seta. Dactylus of P5-P6 short, that of P7 longer. Unguis of P5 bifid but not so outspoken as in P6-P7. Gill present on P5.
